1
00:00:34,994 --> 00:00:36,132
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:36,132 --> 00:00:37,050
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:37,050 --> 00:00:38,142
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:39,421 --> 00:00:42,880
[Gyeongseong Love Song]
With this, I'm thinking of making a movie.

5
00:00:43,954 --> 00:00:45,999
But it doesn't have an ending.

6
00:00:45,999 --> 00:00:47,965
Work on it with me.

7
00:00:52,790 --> 00:00:56,723
You shouldn't have come back
acting as if nothing had happened!

8
00:00:57,930 --> 00:01:00,968
You should've just remained my first love.

9
00:01:00,968 --> 00:01:03,093
Not my biggest regret.

10
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:07,150
<i>My first love, who grew by feeding on my dream,</i>

11
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:09,569
<i>Woo Soo Bin</i>

12
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:11,472
<i>has returned.</i>

13
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:38,146
Cut! Cut!

14
00:02:38,146 --> 00:02:39,946
Lights on!

15
00:02:40,693 --> 00:02:42,773
That was good. Why?

16
00:02:43,739 --> 00:02:46,416
Why would you hold a flashlight?

17
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:47,935
They do in movies.

18
00:02:47,935 --> 00:02:50,003
That's what you call a cliché.

19
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:52,071
What's a cliché?

20
00:02:52,071 --> 00:02:53,915
What's with the blood makeup?

21
00:02:53,915 --> 00:02:55,541
Woo Soo Bin!

22
00:02:55,541 --> 00:02:56,991
Yeah?

23
00:02:56,991 --> 00:03:00,231
Why do you keep spinning that?

24
00:03:00,231 --> 00:03:03,082
You told me to keep spinning it.

25
00:03:03,994 --> 00:03:06,091
Should I reverse it?

26
00:03:06,091 --> 00:03:08,115
Where's the cat?

27
00:03:08,115 --> 00:03:09,398
Kitty.

28
00:03:09,398 --> 00:03:12,906
I think that's enough makeup...

29
00:03:12,906 --> 00:03:15,932
I have a cram school soon.

30
00:03:17,759 --> 00:03:19,545
It's perfect now.

31
00:03:20,399 --> 00:03:23,112
- Thanks.
- Sure.

32
00:03:26,583 --> 00:03:28,333
Makeup's done.

33
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:31,173
Yi Jae, I can't find the cat.

34
00:03:31,173 --> 00:03:34,153
Fine. We already shot the cat scene.

35
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:39,114
This scene feels flat.

36
00:03:40,953 --> 00:03:42,979
It needs a punch.

37
00:03:52,737 --> 00:03:54,269
Here.

38
00:03:54,269 --> 00:03:56,702
You shoot the next take.

39
00:03:56,702 --> 00:03:58,232
Me?

40
00:03:58,232 --> 00:04:00,084
You get the vibe, huh?

41
00:04:01,662 --> 00:04:03,302
Yeah.

42
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:08,104
I'm dying here.

43
00:04:08,104 --> 00:04:09,374
My shoulder...

44
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:11,233
Seriously...

45
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:12,753
He's even worse.

46
00:04:12,753 --> 00:04:15,346
Isn't this makeup a bit much?

47
00:04:15,346 --> 00:04:16,980
Ready!

48
00:04:18,955 --> 00:04:22,270
Woo Soo Bin, you ready?

49
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:23,502
Yeah.

50
00:04:23,502 --> 00:04:25,098
Okay.

51
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,855
Action!

52
00:04:40,197 --> 00:04:44,946
<i>What kind of world does she live in?</i>

53
00:04:49,986 --> 00:04:52,240
<i>What she likes,</i>

54
00:04:57,258 --> 00:04:59,372
<i>what she sees,</i>

55
00:05:05,979 --> 00:05:08,347
<i>what she says...</i>

56
00:05:17,234 --> 00:05:20,147
<i>I wanted to know it all.</i>

57
00:05:26,852 --> 00:05:28,955
What is all this?

58
00:05:28,955 --> 00:05:31,600
What are you doing here?

59
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,542
Get out!

60
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:35,639
[Episode 2]

61
00:05:37,371 --> 00:05:39,349
Get it together.

62
00:05:39,349 --> 00:05:41,415
Oh my gosh.

63
00:05:41,415 --> 00:05:43,516
I haven't even hit you yet.

64
00:05:43,516 --> 00:05:47,647
Ju Yi Jae, you're the problem!

65
00:05:48,311 --> 00:05:49,641
That hurts.

66
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:52,978
Of course it does. That's why I hit you.

67
00:05:52,978 --> 00:05:54,464
Woo Soo Bin!

68
00:05:54,464 --> 00:05:55,917
What about med school?

69
00:05:55,917 --> 00:05:59,651
Senior year is crucial. What are you doing?

70
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:01,971
You're absolutely right.

71
00:06:01,971 --> 00:06:05,229
This shoot is my college exam.

72
00:06:05,229 --> 00:06:09,619
If I win the grand prize,
special admission is a done deal.

73
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:14,322
Do you even know what that means?

74
00:06:14,322 --> 00:06:15,735
Why are you laughing?

75
00:06:15,735 --> 00:06:18,093
Is that so funny?

76
00:06:18,093 --> 00:06:19,603
Listen up.

77
00:06:19,603 --> 00:06:21,277
This is a school!

78
00:06:21,277 --> 00:06:24,154
Quit messing around and study!

79
00:06:24,154 --> 00:06:25,591
- Yes.
- Yes.

80
00:06:25,591 --> 00:06:28,397
- You okay?
- I'm okay.

81
00:06:29,512 --> 00:06:31,195
Nice accent.

82
00:06:31,195 --> 00:06:33,262
You... you okay?

83
00:06:33,262 --> 00:06:35,079
That's right.

84
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:36,522
[Bunam Market]

85
00:06:46,857 --> 00:06:48,922
Let me help you.

86
00:06:55,450 --> 00:06:59,427
Two 5,000-won bags of twist donuts, please.

87
00:06:59,427 --> 00:07:01,857
My mom loves them.

88
00:07:01,857 --> 00:07:03,437
What a good son.

89
00:07:03,437 --> 00:07:05,807
Am I? Aren't you?

90
00:07:05,807 --> 00:07:08,690
No. My mom and I don't get along.

91
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:11,518
You seemed close to me.

92
00:07:11,518 --> 00:07:14,281
That's just how families are.

93
00:07:16,987 --> 00:07:20,187
- So that's normal?
- Thank you.

94
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:33,365
Jeez.

95
00:08:04,357 --> 00:08:05,652
She didn't see us, huh?

96
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:07,047
No.

97
00:08:07,047 --> 00:08:08,632
Come on in.

98
00:08:16,108 --> 00:08:18,508
Ta-da!

99
00:08:18,508 --> 00:08:20,500
What do you think?

100
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,304
Awesome.

101
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,379
[School of Zombie, Ju Yi Jae]

102
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:36,779
Woo Soo Bin.

103
00:08:36,779 --> 00:08:39,124
Not bad.

104
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:45,645
Hey, Yi Jae.

105
00:08:46,305 --> 00:08:49,975
I want to be a movie director too,
just like you.

106
00:08:51,101 --> 00:08:54,992
If I can't skip med school,
I can just fail to get in.

107
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:57,173
I'll bomb the college exam.

108
00:08:57,173 --> 00:08:59,720
Then my dad can't force me, yeah?

109
00:09:04,775 --> 00:09:06,619
Woo Soo Bin.

110
00:09:06,619 --> 00:09:10,396
Do you know how hard this path is?

111
00:09:10,396 --> 00:09:13,342
If this is just a phase, forget it.

112
00:09:13,342 --> 00:09:16,268
You've got a long way to go.

113
00:09:19,255 --> 00:09:21,280
I've thought about it a lot.

114
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,902
I love movies.

115
00:09:22,902 --> 00:09:25,295
You made me see that.

116
00:09:25,295 --> 00:09:26,690
Me?

117
00:09:27,696 --> 00:09:32,242
The world you see is warm and fun.

118
00:09:32,977 --> 00:09:34,770
It's a zombie movie.

119
00:09:36,304 --> 00:09:40,750
Even your zombie world is warm and fun.

120
00:09:42,566 --> 00:09:46,339
I dream of the same world as you.

121
00:09:50,969 --> 00:09:54,481
<i>Woo Soo Bin may never know.</i>

122
00:09:56,773 --> 00:09:58,098
Aren't you leaving?

123
00:09:58,098 --> 00:10:00,554
I'm heading home.

124
00:10:00,554 --> 00:10:04,099
Turn off the lights and lock up later.

125
00:10:05,589 --> 00:10:08,973
What's she doing in there? That's creepy.

126
00:10:08,973 --> 00:10:11,029
She should just study.

127
00:10:34,743 --> 00:10:38,339
<i>Woo Soo Bin may never know.</i>

128
00:10:40,193 --> 00:10:41,839
<i>Yi Jae.</i>

129
00:10:42,684 --> 00:10:44,606
<i>Look good? Acting cool.</i>

130
00:10:44,606 --> 00:10:49,483
<i>The one who brought me
to a warm, joyful world...</i>

131
00:10:51,427 --> 00:10:53,554
<i>was him.</i>

132
00:10:56,714 --> 00:10:57,851
- Soo Bin!
- Yes?

133
00:10:57,851 --> 00:10:59,304
- Aren't you eating?
- No.

134
00:10:59,304 --> 00:11:01,098
- Where are you going?
- To celebrate her!

135
00:11:01,098 --> 00:11:04,397
He must be skipping class to see Yi Jae.

136
00:11:20,709 --> 00:11:23,810
Hey, stop!

137
00:11:42,619 --> 00:11:46,047
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival, Grand Prize]
I won the grand prize!

138
00:11:49,196 --> 00:11:54,432
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival]
My mother once told me to be anyone.

139
00:11:54,432 --> 00:11:58,163
But I don't want to be just anyone.

140
00:11:58,163 --> 00:11:59,595
I was born once!

141
00:11:59,595 --> 00:12:01,555
So I'm going to live this life right!

142
00:12:01,555 --> 00:12:04,900
I believe people come before movies.

143
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:08,205
And people come before directors.

144
00:12:08,205 --> 00:12:12,177
I will become a film director with heart.

145
00:12:12,177 --> 00:12:14,437
Go, Ju Yi Jae!

146
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:20,990
What a bold acceptance speech.

147
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:24,195
Where is her family?

148
00:12:26,752 --> 00:12:28,922
I came alone.

149
00:12:28,922 --> 00:12:32,282
Which is good. No one can take my prize money.

150
00:12:34,528 --> 00:12:37,262
Congratulations, Yi Jae.

151
00:12:42,365 --> 00:12:46,020
Looks like a close friend came.

152
00:12:49,793 --> 00:12:52,167
Congratulations, Yi Jae.

153
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,524
Woo Soo Bin.

154
00:13:02,524 --> 00:13:05,004
Want to hear a secret?

155
00:13:05,877 --> 00:13:10,168
This is why I wanted to be a film director.

156
00:13:10,168 --> 00:13:11,735
Awards.

157
00:13:12,981 --> 00:13:17,978
I won my first writing award in sixth grade.

158
00:13:17,978 --> 00:13:21,555
The way they all looked at me...
I never forgot it.

159
00:13:21,555 --> 00:13:25,354
Looking back,
I think that's where it all started.

160
00:13:26,334 --> 00:13:28,111
Thanks, Soo Bin.

161
00:13:28,111 --> 00:13:30,199
You helped me again.

162
00:13:30,199 --> 00:13:32,104
I didn't do much.

163
00:13:32,104 --> 00:13:35,099
But why is that a secret?

164
00:13:35,919 --> 00:13:40,439
My dream sounds big, but it started so small.

165
00:13:40,439 --> 00:13:45,117
Every great thing starts small.

166
00:13:45,117 --> 00:13:49,771
Like how my feelings for you
became the same dream.

167
00:14:03,172 --> 00:14:06,372
Let's make movies together.

168
00:14:07,665 --> 00:14:09,249
"The Matrix" had two directors.

169
00:14:09,249 --> 00:14:11,671
So did "No Country for Old Men."

170
00:14:15,153 --> 00:14:16,933
What do you think?

171
00:14:17,698 --> 00:14:20,373
- Together?
- Picture this.

172
00:14:20,373 --> 00:14:24,240
Our names, side by side in the credits.

173
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,577
Let's do something great together!

174
00:14:36,207 --> 00:14:37,946
Yeah.

175
00:14:37,946 --> 00:14:40,006
Let's do something great!

176
00:14:40,006 --> 00:14:41,489
Come here.

177
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:46,328
No, don't do it!

178
00:14:46,328 --> 00:14:47,788
It's cold!

179
00:15:33,808 --> 00:15:35,441
I'm sorry.

180
00:16:01,884 --> 00:16:03,884
I'm home.

181
00:16:20,352 --> 00:16:22,860
In my house,

182
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:26,464
not one flaw is allowed.

183
00:16:28,953 --> 00:16:31,066
Objects,

184
00:16:32,207 --> 00:16:34,432
plants,

185
00:16:35,912 --> 00:16:38,061
people...

186
00:16:39,325 --> 00:16:41,465
Same rule.

187
00:17:02,147 --> 00:17:04,039
Do you understand?

188
00:17:06,164 --> 00:17:08,416
Yes, Father.

189
00:17:09,744 --> 00:17:10,814
Are these free?

190
00:17:10,814 --> 00:17:13,434
- Isn't this "Memories of Murder?"
- I loved this one.

191
00:17:13,434 --> 00:17:14,871
Right?

192
00:17:14,871 --> 00:17:17,084
Wait. That's mine!

193
00:17:17,084 --> 00:17:18,851
- What?
- That's mine.

194
00:17:18,851 --> 00:17:20,641
What the...

195
00:17:20,641 --> 00:17:22,167
Let's just go.

196
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:25,599
- What a weirdo.
- Let's go.

197
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:26,932
[Free: Take Them All!]

198
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:35,576
Mom!

199
00:17:35,576 --> 00:17:37,432
I'm not deaf, girl.

200
00:17:37,432 --> 00:17:39,643
I told you not to toss these!

201
00:17:39,643 --> 00:17:42,215
Why keep tapes in a noodle shop?

202
00:17:42,215 --> 00:17:45,639
- They're not worth a dime.
- What are you talking about?

203
00:17:45,639 --> 00:17:48,742
- They're worth money.
- "Worth money?"

204
00:17:48,742 --> 00:17:51,392
To me, they're dead weight!

205
00:17:51,392 --> 00:17:53,539
I said don't toss them!

206
00:17:53,539 --> 00:17:55,182
I won today!

207
00:17:55,182 --> 00:17:57,909
The prize is one million won.

208
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:01,084
Good.

209
00:18:01,084 --> 00:18:03,870
Put it toward your dad's gas.

210
00:18:03,870 --> 00:18:07,297
No, I'm putting another table here.

211
00:18:07,297 --> 00:18:10,205
Another table? This place is always dead.

212
00:18:10,205 --> 00:18:12,167
Watch your mouth.

213
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:15,512
Why? You talk to me like that all the time!

214
00:18:15,512 --> 00:18:18,195
Did I ask for money? Or to study abroad?

215
00:18:18,195 --> 00:18:20,541
I don't ask for anything!

216
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:24,151
Just leave me alone!

217
00:18:24,151 --> 00:18:26,144
God, you're loud.

218
00:18:26,144 --> 00:18:27,435
Fine.

219
00:18:27,435 --> 00:18:30,152
Stuff them in storage
or keep them in your room.

220
00:18:30,152 --> 00:18:32,288
Do whatever you want!

221
00:18:48,032 --> 00:18:49,758
Yi Jae.

222
00:18:59,911 --> 00:19:01,557
Were you crying?

223
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:04,421
Why? What happened?

224
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:06,885
I'm fine.

225
00:19:06,885 --> 00:19:11,459
Just paying my dues to become a legend.

226
00:19:11,459 --> 00:19:13,009
What?

227
00:19:14,223 --> 00:19:16,427
What are you doing here?

228
00:19:20,203 --> 00:19:22,096
Telepathy?

229
00:19:24,791 --> 00:19:26,888
Woo Soo Bin.

230
00:19:26,888 --> 00:19:30,871
You know The Fox and the Grapes?

231
00:19:30,871 --> 00:19:32,375
What's that?

232
00:19:32,375 --> 00:19:36,556
A fox wanted grapes hanging way up high.

233
00:19:36,556 --> 00:19:39,488
He tried everything, but couldn't reach them.

234
00:19:39,488 --> 00:19:42,348
Know what he said?

235
00:19:42,348 --> 00:19:43,988
No idea.

236
00:19:44,657 --> 00:19:46,728
"They're probably sour anyway."

237
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:49,323
Then he gave up.

238
00:19:49,323 --> 00:19:53,592
The fox said it in that accent?

239
00:19:54,252 --> 00:19:56,916
That's not the point.

240
00:19:56,916 --> 00:19:59,760
You're hopeless.

241
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,579
Sorry.

242
00:20:02,175 --> 00:20:06,133
But maybe they really were sour.

243
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:07,891
So what?

244
00:20:07,891 --> 00:20:11,193
At least he tried them.

245
00:20:11,193 --> 00:20:13,600
If they're bad, spit them out.

246
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:18,323
You know... Trying beats never trying.

247
00:20:18,323 --> 00:20:22,253
So quitters and finishers are different?

248
00:20:22,253 --> 00:20:23,737
- Right?
- Exactly.

249
00:20:23,737 --> 00:20:25,414
Just watch me.

250
00:20:25,414 --> 00:20:27,157
When I say it, I do it.

251
00:20:27,157 --> 00:20:29,980
Even if it kills me.

252
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:32,337
Don't let it kill you.

253
00:20:32,337 --> 00:20:34,237
Call me instead.

254
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:38,664
Wherever you are, I'll come running.

255
00:20:38,664 --> 00:20:41,496
Stand on my shoulders.

256
00:20:57,639 --> 00:21:00,263
<i>I meant every word.</i>

257
00:21:00,263 --> 00:21:03,878
<i>I would've given her everything I had.</i>

258
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:11,092
[First Short Film - Woo Soo Bin]

259
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:16,472
<i>After all,
my world was the one she made for me.</i>

260
00:21:42,292 --> 00:21:44,552
[Let's meet at six today. No excuses!]

261
00:22:02,823 --> 00:22:06,584
[Directed/filmed/edited by Woo Soo Bin]

262
00:22:09,511 --> 00:22:11,187
Romance.

263
00:22:15,172 --> 00:22:17,909
Why are you crying?

264
00:22:17,909 --> 00:22:20,510
Let's write a romance together.

265
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:22,653
An amazing one.

266
00:22:22,653 --> 00:22:23,753
Out of nowhere?

267
00:22:23,753 --> 00:22:25,596
It hit me!

268
00:22:25,596 --> 00:22:26,684
Hey.

269
00:22:26,684 --> 00:22:29,916
Do you know what a director needs most?

270
00:22:29,916 --> 00:22:31,740
Writing is a given.

271
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:35,633
You need eyes that see the world.

272
00:22:35,633 --> 00:22:37,413
You pass!

273
00:22:38,019 --> 00:22:39,735
Want to kiss?

274
00:22:40,913 --> 00:22:43,171
- What?
- First love. First kiss.

275
00:22:43,171 --> 00:22:45,477
This feels like the scene.

276
00:22:45,477 --> 00:22:47,574
This movie. You.

277
00:22:47,574 --> 00:22:49,474
And this heart.

278
00:22:49,474 --> 00:22:51,767
It feels like now.

279
00:23:08,897 --> 00:23:11,070
Come on.

280
00:23:12,051 --> 00:23:14,791
How can you say that with a straight face?

281
00:23:14,791 --> 00:23:17,821
I'm really nervous now.

282
00:23:19,041 --> 00:23:20,474
Fine.

283
00:23:21,241 --> 00:23:26,512
If we both get into film school,
I'll kiss you first.

284
00:23:26,512 --> 00:23:28,716
How can I wait that long?

285
00:23:31,810 --> 00:23:35,894
If we do it now, I might not stop.

286
00:23:35,894 --> 00:23:37,670
Stop what?

287
00:23:43,603 --> 00:23:47,955
Seniors have a lot to hold back.

288
00:23:47,955 --> 00:23:50,094
I'm a senior too.

289
00:23:52,067 --> 00:23:53,498
Right.

290
00:23:53,498 --> 00:23:55,498
Only you're a senior.

291
00:23:58,487 --> 00:24:01,890
Nan Young, a gisaeng with a dream.

292
00:24:01,890 --> 00:24:03,685
But then,

293
00:24:03,685 --> 00:24:08,034
as if by fate, a man appeared.

294
00:24:08,034 --> 00:24:09,908
He was shot dead.

295
00:24:09,908 --> 00:24:12,786
How do they fall in love?

296
00:24:12,786 --> 00:24:14,975
Love at first sight?

297
00:24:14,975 --> 00:24:17,726
- Did you fall for me at first sight?
- What?

298
00:24:20,823 --> 00:24:21,927
Yeah.

299
00:24:21,927 --> 00:24:24,861
Okay, love at first sight it is.

300
00:24:24,861 --> 00:24:27,216
- Need something cooler.
- A fountain pen?

301
00:24:27,216 --> 00:24:28,251
Or a watch...

302
00:24:28,251 --> 00:24:31,992
Maybe we can make his face stand out.

303
00:24:35,048 --> 00:24:37,406
So he dies in the end?

304
00:24:37,406 --> 00:24:39,405
- Hold on.
- What?

305
00:24:39,405 --> 00:24:42,414
Fine, you're the genius!

306
00:24:43,931 --> 00:24:45,735
Yi Jae...

307
00:24:45,735 --> 00:24:47,486
I'm sorry.

308
00:24:51,313 --> 00:24:53,033
Forget it.

309
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,239
How about this?

310
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:20,117
When you pick grapes, hold them by the bottom.

311
00:25:20,117 --> 00:25:23,814
That way, they won't get damaged.

312
00:25:23,814 --> 00:25:25,954
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

313
00:25:25,954 --> 00:25:28,960
- Hold the bottom like this...
- Firmly.

314
00:25:32,664 --> 00:25:34,854
- Like this?
- That's right.

315
00:25:34,854 --> 00:25:38,235
I raised them like my own kids. No chemicals.

316
00:25:38,235 --> 00:25:40,506
- So treat each one with care.
- Oh, you're here.

317
00:25:40,506 --> 00:25:42,044
- Hello.
- This way.

318
00:25:42,044 --> 00:25:43,944
Thanks for coming.

319
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,075
May I?

320
00:25:51,075 --> 00:25:53,075
Just a second.

321
00:26:09,211 --> 00:26:11,655
Hello, sir.

322
00:26:11,655 --> 00:26:13,655
- Welcome.
- Hello.

323
00:26:17,818 --> 00:26:19,903
Hello, Ju Yi Jae.

324
00:26:19,903 --> 00:26:21,743
I'm Ian Woo.

325
00:26:28,008 --> 00:26:29,991
Producer Kyung, what is this?

326
00:26:29,991 --> 00:26:31,111
"This?"

327
00:26:31,111 --> 00:26:32,676
He's today's special guest.

328
00:26:32,676 --> 00:26:34,700
You don't like the flowers?

329
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:37,058
Since when do we have guests?

330
00:26:37,058 --> 00:26:39,143
- Since today...
- Without a pre-interview?

331
00:26:39,143 --> 00:26:40,453
I'll just pick some grapes.

332
00:26:40,453 --> 00:26:42,283
You're here to become a farmer?

333
00:26:42,283 --> 00:26:43,689
Maybe.

334
00:26:43,689 --> 00:26:45,515
That depends on you.

335
00:26:48,066 --> 00:26:51,030
All right, say hello to...

336
00:26:53,178 --> 00:26:54,615
She must be busy.

337
00:26:54,615 --> 00:26:57,284
You even brought flowers?

338
00:26:57,284 --> 00:26:59,288
Thank you.

339
00:26:59,288 --> 00:27:01,008
Beautiful.

340
00:27:05,146 --> 00:27:06,997
I'm a huge fan.

341
00:27:06,997 --> 00:27:08,324
Me too.

342
00:27:08,324 --> 00:27:09,713
Congrats on the award.

343
00:27:09,713 --> 00:27:15,347
I know this was last-minute,
but this feels wrong.

344
00:27:15,347 --> 00:27:18,257
Let's wing it. He's just picking grapes.

345
00:27:18,257 --> 00:27:20,736
Do you know him? You're into movies.

346
00:27:20,736 --> 00:27:23,058
I'd know Bong Joon Ho or Park Chan Wook.

347
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:24,138
Yeah?

348
00:27:24,138 --> 00:27:27,825
I looked him up,
and it's all about his first love.

349
00:27:27,825 --> 00:27:29,441
Let's dig into that.

350
00:27:29,441 --> 00:27:32,486
A young, handsome director and his love story.

351
00:27:32,486 --> 00:27:37,114
Young, handsome... That's a bit much.

352
00:27:39,019 --> 00:27:42,296
Honestly, he could pass for an actor.

353
00:27:42,296 --> 00:27:45,983
You could be an actor.

354
00:27:45,983 --> 00:27:48,200
That's a stretch.

355
00:27:49,325 --> 00:27:50,476
By the way,

356
00:27:50,476 --> 00:27:53,449
his first love story is already everywhere.

357
00:27:53,449 --> 00:27:55,895
- Do we really need it too?
- Huh?

358
00:27:55,895 --> 00:27:58,276
You said you didn't know him.

359
00:27:58,936 --> 00:28:00,796
Right. I don't.

360
00:28:01,571 --> 00:28:03,548
Can you take a picture of us?

361
00:28:03,548 --> 00:28:06,686
- Look at him. What a hit.
- Thank you.

362
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:10,729
Please stand over here.

363
00:28:11,387 --> 00:28:12,978
- Here we go.
- Okay.

364
00:28:12,978 --> 00:28:15,287
One, two, cheese.

365
00:28:15,287 --> 00:28:16,697
Finger hearts.

366
00:28:16,697 --> 00:28:18,428
One, two...

367
00:28:18,428 --> 00:28:20,492
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

368
00:28:20,492 --> 00:28:23,036
- We'll go get ready.
- Okay, thank you.

369
00:28:23,036 --> 00:28:25,414
- See you soon.
- Yeah.

370
00:28:30,734 --> 00:28:32,164
What?

371
00:28:35,357 --> 00:28:37,559
Psycho.

372
00:28:37,559 --> 00:28:40,396
- Today, on this farm...
- Ms. Ju Yi Jae.

373
00:28:40,396 --> 00:28:42,121
I look forward to this.

374
00:28:42,121 --> 00:28:46,506
We've never had a surprise guest before.

375
00:28:46,506 --> 00:28:49,543
Please answer each question nicely and clearly.

376
00:28:49,543 --> 00:28:52,097
Talking back is your specialty, huh?

377
00:28:52,097 --> 00:28:54,247
Producer Kyung has the flowers.

378
00:28:54,247 --> 00:28:55,989
Make sure you take them.

379
00:28:55,989 --> 00:28:58,376
You never revealed your real name anywhere.

380
00:28:58,376 --> 00:29:00,706
Must be a lot you're hiding.

381
00:29:00,706 --> 00:29:02,781
Was that on the card?

382
00:29:02,781 --> 00:29:05,261
Yeah, that was personal.

383
00:29:05,261 --> 00:29:07,285
Your real name is Woo Soo Bin. Next.

384
00:29:07,285 --> 00:29:09,101
What are your future plans?

385
00:29:09,101 --> 00:29:11,585
Why did you come on our show?

386
00:29:11,585 --> 00:29:13,091
Oh, right.

387
00:29:13,091 --> 00:29:15,171
Why are you here?

388
00:29:19,910 --> 00:29:21,629
To see you.

389
00:29:22,223 --> 00:29:25,580
When did this start?

390
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:27,750
The station?

391
00:29:27,750 --> 00:29:29,774
The online deal?

392
00:29:29,774 --> 00:29:31,144
From here...

393
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:33,592
What are you doing?

394
00:29:35,267 --> 00:29:36,919
I pulled a few strings.

395
00:29:36,919 --> 00:29:38,797
And the online deal?

396
00:29:38,797 --> 00:29:40,771
I heard Yu Geon talking to you.

397
00:29:40,771 --> 00:29:42,533
Yu Geon, that little...

398
00:29:42,533 --> 00:29:44,449
That's a lot of questions.

399
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:47,654
Are you curious too?

400
00:29:47,654 --> 00:29:49,205
I'll answer everything.

401
00:29:49,205 --> 00:29:51,803
Even about my first love, if you want.

402
00:29:51,803 --> 00:29:53,068
You little...

403
00:29:53,068 --> 00:29:55,420
I'm kidding.

404
00:29:55,420 --> 00:29:57,711
- You looked too nervous.
- Come on.

405
00:29:57,711 --> 00:29:59,081
Who says I'm nervous?

406
00:29:59,081 --> 00:30:02,420
You keep biting your lip.

407
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:04,364
That's your tell.

408
00:30:04,364 --> 00:30:06,266
You'll make it bleed.

409
00:30:08,462 --> 00:30:11,258
Hey. Woo Soo Bin.

410
00:30:11,258 --> 00:30:14,361
- Yeah?
- Try anything...

411
00:30:24,116 --> 00:30:25,867
Stand by.

412
00:30:25,867 --> 00:30:27,602
Cue!

413
00:30:27,602 --> 00:30:29,266
Hello, viewers!

414
00:30:29,266 --> 00:30:31,582
I'm Ju Yi Jae of Here Comes Yi Jae.

415
00:30:31,582 --> 00:30:37,129
We go wherever you are, all across the country.

416
00:30:37,129 --> 00:30:40,812
So where am I today?

417
00:30:40,812 --> 00:30:44,550
This sun, this breeze, this perfect weather...

418
00:30:44,550 --> 00:30:46,390
Can you feel it?

419
00:30:47,759 --> 00:30:50,183
And that fresh scent of grapes.

420
00:30:52,378 --> 00:30:54,523
She's really good.

421
00:30:54,523 --> 00:30:56,315
Sorry?

422
00:30:56,315 --> 00:30:58,483
- Please stand by.
- Got it.

423
00:30:58,483 --> 00:31:03,797
A major event in European cinema,
the European International Film Awards.

424
00:31:03,797 --> 00:31:05,094
He won two awards there.

425
00:31:05,094 --> 00:31:07,201
Please welcome Director Ian Woo!

426
00:31:07,201 --> 00:31:09,780
Hello, Director.

427
00:31:09,780 --> 00:31:11,205
Hello.

428
00:31:11,205 --> 00:31:13,248
I'm Ian Woo, a filmmaker.

429
00:31:13,248 --> 00:31:18,179
It's an honor to be on this show.

430
00:31:18,179 --> 00:31:21,848
Can we count on you today?

431
00:31:21,848 --> 00:31:24,105
I'll do my best.

432
00:31:24,105 --> 00:31:26,844
Let's do this!

433
00:31:28,054 --> 00:31:31,770
- Looking forward to today.
- Same here.

434
00:31:32,361 --> 00:31:34,147
Cut!

435
00:31:39,224 --> 00:31:41,514
Is she always like that?

436
00:31:41,514 --> 00:31:42,930
Well...

437
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:51,285
What does "Wandering," the film that
brought you a major award, mean to you?

438
00:31:51,285 --> 00:31:55,027
It's special because it's my first feature.

439
00:31:55,027 --> 00:31:56,732
But I think

440
00:31:56,732 --> 00:32:00,565
it's even more precious to me
because it gave me a second chance.

441
00:32:00,565 --> 00:32:03,078
What do you mean by that?

442
00:32:04,058 --> 00:32:08,429
If I'm nobody, who would care about my story?

443
00:32:08,429 --> 00:32:11,073
I had to become a director first
if I wanted to do what I wanted.

444
00:32:11,073 --> 00:32:16,042
So "Wandering" was made with that calculation

445
00:32:16,042 --> 00:32:17,680
in mind.

446
00:32:19,287 --> 00:32:20,912
Did that sound too full of myself?

447
00:32:20,912 --> 00:32:25,024
No. It sounded very realistic.

448
00:32:25,024 --> 00:32:30,451
From a distance,
the world of film seems so romantic.

449
00:32:30,451 --> 00:32:34,021
Now I'm preparing my next film
for that romance.

450
00:32:34,021 --> 00:32:36,441
That's why I came back to Korea.

451
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,601
The title is

452
00:32:40,417 --> 00:32:42,314
"Gyeongseong Love Song."

453
00:32:54,131 --> 00:32:55,291
[Sim Yu Geon]

454
00:33:00,252 --> 00:33:03,399
If you told me to die, I would.

455
00:33:04,058 --> 00:33:07,838
- Here's my profile.
- It's already right there.

456
00:33:07,838 --> 00:33:10,249
He still likes you when your ramyeon sucks?

457
00:33:10,249 --> 00:33:12,604
That's true love.

458
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:20,751
[Profile submissions closed]

459
00:33:37,202 --> 00:33:38,946
Hey!

460
00:33:38,946 --> 00:33:40,884
What took you so long?

461
00:33:40,884 --> 00:33:42,384
I'm not the delivery.

462
00:33:42,384 --> 00:33:44,856
Huh? I'll call you back.

463
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,576
What did you say?

464
00:33:51,464 --> 00:33:53,416
Hi, Team Lead Kang.

465
00:33:53,416 --> 00:33:55,662
It's me, Sim Yu Geon.

466
00:33:55,662 --> 00:33:57,406
Sim Yu Geon?

467
00:33:57,406 --> 00:33:59,828
Here's my profile.

468
00:34:01,414 --> 00:34:04,217
So you moved here.

469
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,978
You don't remember me?

470
00:34:06,978 --> 00:34:09,558
You were with Actor Team Three.

471
00:34:09,558 --> 00:34:11,301
It's been a while.

472
00:34:11,301 --> 00:34:13,370
- How have you been?
- Fine.

473
00:34:13,370 --> 00:34:16,926
And it's Director now.

474
00:34:17,725 --> 00:34:20,751
You kept yourself up.

475
00:34:21,745 --> 00:34:24,375
That was five, six years ago...

476
00:34:24,375 --> 00:34:28,525
You must be around 30 now.

477
00:34:28,525 --> 00:34:32,029
- I turn 30 next year.
- Yeah, right.

478
00:34:32,029 --> 00:34:33,699
Did you serve?

479
00:34:33,699 --> 00:34:37,164
Yes. Right after I left the company.

480
00:34:38,181 --> 00:34:40,872
"Left the company?"

481
00:34:42,044 --> 00:34:45,502
The CEO scammed us,
and the company vanished overnight.

482
00:34:45,502 --> 00:34:48,143
What a nice way to put it.

483
00:34:48,774 --> 00:34:51,431
You're too nice.

484
00:34:54,654 --> 00:34:55,918
Well...

485
00:34:55,918 --> 00:34:58,563
It's all in the past now.

486
00:34:58,563 --> 00:35:00,583
Gosh.

487
00:35:00,583 --> 00:35:02,895
That's why you're failing.

488
00:35:02,895 --> 00:35:04,146
I can tell just by looking.

489
00:35:04,146 --> 00:35:07,111
Whether someone will make it or not.

490
00:35:07,111 --> 00:35:09,561
Anyway, Yu Geon.

491
00:35:09,561 --> 00:35:12,151
You're not young. Move on.

492
00:35:12,151 --> 00:35:15,989
I'm saying this for your own good.

493
00:35:15,989 --> 00:35:21,757
We were once at the same agency.
So I do feel bad.

494
00:35:21,757 --> 00:35:23,368
There it is.

495
00:35:23,368 --> 00:35:24,858
Bye.

496
00:35:25,457 --> 00:35:28,708
- What took you so long?
- Sorry.

497
00:35:29,844 --> 00:35:31,645
Remember that.

498
00:35:53,501 --> 00:35:56,718
- Sure.
- Ma'am, your lunch is here.

499
00:35:56,718 --> 00:35:58,649
Ha Na loves the script.

500
00:35:58,649 --> 00:36:00,870
She's dying to do it.

501
00:36:00,870 --> 00:36:04,116
Her shoot wraps soon. She can start right away.

502
00:36:04,796 --> 00:36:07,928
Of course. Bye.

503
00:36:11,263 --> 00:36:13,733
Since when am I dying to do it?

504
00:36:13,733 --> 00:36:14,985
Looks good.

505
00:36:14,985 --> 00:36:18,150
Then again, do I ever get a choice?

506
00:36:18,150 --> 00:36:20,040
Not for you.

507
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:21,928
You have a dress to fit into.

508
00:36:21,928 --> 00:36:23,468
Skip it.

509
00:36:24,350 --> 00:36:28,027
I had to delay that scene
while you lost weight.

510
00:36:28,027 --> 00:36:31,223
Then change the dress!

511
00:36:31,223 --> 00:36:33,597
I'm taking a break after this.

512
00:36:33,597 --> 00:36:35,645
Don't send me scripts.

513
00:36:36,303 --> 00:36:39,827
You think scripts just come to you?

514
00:36:39,827 --> 00:36:41,471
An actress's career is short.

515
00:36:41,471 --> 00:36:43,829
One day, the world will move on.

516
00:36:43,829 --> 00:36:45,581
Don't rest now.

517
00:36:45,581 --> 00:36:47,571
Then when do I rest?

518
00:36:47,571 --> 00:36:49,958
- After I get married like you?
- Yes.

519
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:53,095
Then use your kid for a comeback.

520
00:36:53,095 --> 00:36:54,399
Hey.

521
00:36:54,399 --> 00:36:56,498
Be proud.

522
00:36:57,148 --> 00:36:59,778
She started the parenting-show craze.

523
00:36:59,778 --> 00:37:01,172
I see.

524
00:37:01,172 --> 00:37:03,796
Don't forget that.

525
00:37:03,796 --> 00:37:05,847
That was my popularity.

526
00:37:05,847 --> 00:37:08,862
- Right.
- I made it happen.

527
00:37:08,862 --> 00:37:11,338
I'm going to the salon.

528
00:37:11,962 --> 00:37:13,446
Sorry?

529
00:37:13,446 --> 00:37:14,570
Already?

530
00:37:14,570 --> 00:37:16,860
We still have time. Let me eat...

531
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:18,617
Let's go.

532
00:37:22,299 --> 00:37:24,417
- Keep her hair down.
- Got it.

533
00:37:24,417 --> 00:37:27,200
Ha Na, wait!

534
00:37:29,208 --> 00:37:34,379
Welcome to the press event for
"10 Reasons Contract Marriage Is Dangerous."

535
00:37:34,379 --> 00:37:38,342
First, please welcome Oh Ha Na,
who plays Lee Yoon A.

536
00:37:38,342 --> 00:37:40,576
Now for photo time.

537
00:37:40,576 --> 00:37:41,702
[Press Event]

538
00:37:46,089 --> 00:37:48,647
They look amazing.

539
00:37:48,647 --> 00:37:50,927
A heart with the director... Great.

540
00:37:50,927 --> 00:37:52,900
I have a question for Oh Ha Na.

541
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:56,806
Your mother, CEO An Su Hui,
was also an actress.

542
00:37:56,806 --> 00:38:00,338
What advice did she give you this time?

543
00:38:01,642 --> 00:38:04,023
She always gives me plenty of advice

544
00:38:04,023 --> 00:38:07,917
as a strict senior and a reliable CEO.

545
00:38:07,917 --> 00:38:10,983
But this time...

546
00:38:10,983 --> 00:38:16,299
She talked more about
why marriage is dangerous.

547
00:38:17,925 --> 00:38:19,235
I see.

548
00:38:19,235 --> 00:38:23,838
How was your chemistry with Ha Na
as a married couple?

549
00:38:25,584 --> 00:38:28,348
I guess

550
00:38:28,348 --> 00:38:32,839
since Ha Na has never dated...
she didn't really get it.

551
00:38:34,444 --> 00:38:37,850
I never said I've never dated.

552
00:38:37,850 --> 00:38:41,667
She debuted over 20 years ago
and never had one dating rumor.

553
00:38:41,667 --> 00:38:43,699
That says it all.

554
00:38:43,699 --> 00:38:45,720
Am I wrong?

555
00:38:51,534 --> 00:38:54,127
Do you like me?

556
00:38:54,127 --> 00:38:55,912
What?

557
00:38:57,093 --> 00:39:01,017
Their back-and-forth
already feels like a drama scene.

558
00:39:01,017 --> 00:39:04,155
This makes us even more excited.

559
00:39:04,155 --> 00:39:05,301
Then shall we...

560
00:39:05,301 --> 00:39:07,744
What? "Do you like me?"

561
00:39:07,744 --> 00:39:11,188
What man would like that temper?

562
00:39:11,188 --> 00:39:13,643
Hey.

563
00:39:13,643 --> 00:39:17,115
I let her name go first.
And I entered after her too?

564
00:39:17,115 --> 00:39:18,181
That's too much.

565
00:39:18,181 --> 00:39:19,322
Well...

566
00:39:19,322 --> 00:39:22,722
The company will paint you as a gentleman.

567
00:39:22,722 --> 00:39:26,339
That hurts my pride. Darn it.

568
00:39:26,339 --> 00:39:28,229
How much does she make per episode?

569
00:39:28,229 --> 00:39:30,523
Don't tell me she makes more too.

570
00:39:30,523 --> 00:39:31,793
Of course not.

571
00:39:31,793 --> 00:39:34,113
You're the male lead.

572
00:39:34,113 --> 00:39:36,450
Without her mom, she's nothing.

573
00:39:36,450 --> 00:39:38,743
And I'm supposed to bow to her?

574
00:39:38,743 --> 00:39:41,215
Everyone knows she's Mommy's little girl.

575
00:39:41,215 --> 00:39:43,486
Even my neighbor's dog knows.

576
00:39:43,486 --> 00:39:44,968
Just close the door.

577
00:39:44,968 --> 00:39:46,951
Mommy!

578
00:39:46,951 --> 00:39:49,324
I'm so upset right now.

579
00:39:49,324 --> 00:39:52,302
That jerk Go Sang Yeon
called me Mommy's little girl!

580
00:39:52,302 --> 00:39:54,594
- Please yell at him.
- CEO An!

581
00:39:54,594 --> 00:39:57,206
That's not what I meant...

582
00:39:57,206 --> 00:39:59,726
Darn it.

583
00:40:00,383 --> 00:40:03,109
Are you insane? What are you doing?

584
00:40:03,109 --> 00:40:05,239
Yes. I'm insane.

585
00:40:05,239 --> 00:40:09,342
You're scared of my mom, idiot.

586
00:40:12,648 --> 00:40:14,592
Hey, get over here.

587
00:40:14,592 --> 00:40:16,959
I said get over here!

588
00:40:16,959 --> 00:40:18,256
- Let's just go.
- Hey!

589
00:40:18,256 --> 00:40:19,990
You little...

590
00:40:19,990 --> 00:40:21,782
Get over here!

591
00:40:22,554 --> 00:40:24,617
<i>Okay, drone shot is next.</i>

592
00:40:24,617 --> 00:40:29,385
<i>We're cleared to ride, so we'll take the truck.</i>

593
00:40:40,929 --> 00:40:43,755
You know The Fox and the Grapes?

594
00:40:44,907 --> 00:40:49,625
A fox tried to reach some grapes,
but he couldn't.

595
00:40:49,625 --> 00:40:52,487
So what did he do?

596
00:40:53,198 --> 00:40:54,376
Not sure.

597
00:40:54,376 --> 00:40:56,574
"They're probably sour anyway."

598
00:40:56,574 --> 00:40:58,564
"Good thing I didn't eat them."

599
00:40:58,564 --> 00:41:00,858
He rationalized it.

600
00:41:00,858 --> 00:41:03,295
Maybe they really were sour.

601
00:41:03,295 --> 00:41:06,315
You never know until you try.

602
00:41:06,315 --> 00:41:09,019
Sadly, the fox will never know.

603
00:41:09,019 --> 00:41:11,752
All that time for one grape?

604
00:41:11,752 --> 00:41:15,413
Not if he got it. But he didn't.

605
00:41:15,413 --> 00:41:16,897
He climbed the tree.

606
00:41:16,897 --> 00:41:20,230
He even used a ladder,
but still couldn't reach.

607
00:41:20,230 --> 00:41:22,647
He hurt his hand. He hurt his leg.

608
00:41:22,647 --> 00:41:25,376
Someone even kicked the ladder away.

609
00:41:25,376 --> 00:41:27,106
And he still shouldn't quit?

610
00:41:27,106 --> 00:41:29,626
What if a friend came to help?

611
00:41:32,158 --> 00:41:36,581
If he stepped on that friend's back,
he could reach them.

612
00:41:36,581 --> 00:41:39,399
<i>Stand on my shoulders.</i>

613
00:41:42,562 --> 00:41:44,968
That friend might snatch them first.

614
00:41:44,968 --> 00:41:48,854
Then he wasted his time and got hurt.

615
00:41:49,632 --> 00:41:52,119
- Yi Jae. You think I took it?
- Are you crazy?

616
00:41:52,119 --> 00:41:54,419
The mic is on.

617
00:41:57,394 --> 00:41:58,565
<i>What's going on?</i>

618
00:41:58,565 --> 00:42:01,593
<i>Why grab his collar?</i>

619
00:42:04,759 --> 00:42:07,329
His shirt button came off!

620
00:42:07,329 --> 00:42:11,040
Must be the wind. That scared me.

621
00:42:12,980 --> 00:42:15,444
<i>Are you okay, sir?</i>

622
00:42:15,444 --> 00:42:19,863
Buttons are falling like leaves.

623
00:42:19,863 --> 00:42:22,089
Must be autumn.

624
00:42:22,089 --> 00:42:23,973
He must be flustered too.

625
00:42:23,973 --> 00:42:26,402
He's just saying anything.

626
00:42:27,575 --> 00:42:29,053
Ju Yi Jae!

627
00:42:29,053 --> 00:42:32,180
- Sew it on when you get off.
- Okay.

628
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:34,433
That scared me.

629
00:43:03,263 --> 00:43:05,287
Thirty million.

630
00:43:05,287 --> 00:43:08,533
- What?
- For the script. I'll sell it.

631
00:43:08,533 --> 00:43:11,399
You need my okay to make it.

632
00:43:13,273 --> 00:43:16,403
I want to finish this story with you.

633
00:43:16,403 --> 00:43:19,086
If you won't, it means nothing to me.

634
00:43:19,086 --> 00:43:21,283
It's just old pages.

635
00:43:21,283 --> 00:43:22,669
Yeah?

636
00:43:22,669 --> 00:43:23,986
Then burn it.

637
00:43:23,986 --> 00:43:26,107
I don't care.

638
00:43:27,554 --> 00:43:29,796
You said I stole it.

639
00:43:30,970 --> 00:43:33,134
You said I was your regret.

640
00:43:34,164 --> 00:43:37,134
I don't want to be that to you.

641
00:43:37,134 --> 00:43:39,817
That's why I can't give up.

642
00:43:55,208 --> 00:43:59,791
I'll return the dream I stole from you.

643
00:43:59,791 --> 00:44:02,222
Even your first love, if you want.

644
00:44:05,921 --> 00:44:09,988
How do I give that back?

645
00:44:15,694 --> 00:44:17,477
What do I do?

646
00:44:23,772 --> 00:44:25,443
Should I?

647
00:44:29,854 --> 00:44:32,187
We're not in high school anymore.

648
00:44:33,325 --> 00:44:35,325
No reason to hold back.

649
00:44:47,145 --> 00:44:49,222
You bastard.

650
00:45:00,258 --> 00:45:02,046
Woo Soo Bin!

651
00:45:03,328 --> 00:45:05,411
Woo Soo Bin!

652
00:45:32,662 --> 00:45:34,817
I'm leaving!

653
00:45:55,562 --> 00:45:58,448
The lights are on...

654
00:46:34,256 --> 00:46:36,242
Thank God.

655
00:46:38,254 --> 00:46:39,975
Why are you skipping school?

656
00:46:39,975 --> 00:46:42,508
Why won't you answer my calls?

657
00:46:42,508 --> 00:46:45,668
Our film school exam is tomorrow.

658
00:46:45,668 --> 00:46:47,907
I'm not going.

659
00:46:49,081 --> 00:46:50,831
You go alone.

660
00:46:50,831 --> 00:46:53,006
I came out to tell you that.

661
00:46:53,006 --> 00:46:54,425
Why?

662
00:46:55,051 --> 00:46:57,563
I'm going to America.

663
00:46:57,563 --> 00:47:00,212
I have to become a doctor.

664
00:47:00,212 --> 00:47:03,029
But you don't want to be a doctor.

665
00:47:04,027 --> 00:47:05,930
What does that matter?

666
00:47:09,981 --> 00:47:11,408
You should go.

667
00:47:22,070 --> 00:47:26,401
Look. We wrote all this.
It doesn't even have an ending.

668
00:47:26,401 --> 00:47:28,697
You can't just leave.

669
00:47:28,697 --> 00:47:30,831
You wanted to direct movies too.

670
00:47:30,831 --> 00:47:33,509
You said you found a dream.

671
00:47:36,607 --> 00:47:40,566
It was just a passing dream.

672
00:47:41,782 --> 00:47:44,168
It was never going to happen.

673
00:47:45,808 --> 00:47:47,836
That's a lie.

674
00:47:47,836 --> 00:47:49,378
That's a lie.

675
00:47:49,378 --> 00:47:51,382
It's not true.

676
00:47:51,382 --> 00:47:53,606
You don't want to go to America!

677
00:47:53,606 --> 00:47:54,791
You promised!

678
00:47:54,791 --> 00:47:57,320
We'd make movies together!

679
00:47:59,559 --> 00:48:01,936
You promised...

680
00:48:19,313 --> 00:48:20,479
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

681
00:48:21,586 --> 00:48:23,750
Then you take this.

682
00:48:23,750 --> 00:48:26,250
You know what this means.

683
00:48:26,250 --> 00:48:28,187
You choose.

684
00:48:28,187 --> 00:48:30,187
I'll be waiting.

685
00:48:31,595 --> 00:48:33,086
Yi Jae.

686
00:48:33,854 --> 00:48:35,660
Ju Yi Jae!

687
00:48:39,918 --> 00:48:43,346
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

688
00:48:45,640 --> 00:48:47,542
[Express Bus: Seoul-Bunam]

689
00:48:50,597 --> 00:48:52,755
[Bus Ticket]
[From Bunam to Seoul]

690
00:49:02,574 --> 00:49:05,146
The bus is leaving now.

691
00:49:19,802 --> 00:49:22,818
Wait! I need to get off!

692
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:32,551
[Operating Room]

693
00:50:37,692 --> 00:50:39,618
Honey...

694
00:50:44,679 --> 00:50:47,057
What do we do?

695
00:50:47,057 --> 00:50:49,103
My daughter...

696
00:51:39,094 --> 00:51:42,335
Ms. Ju Yi Jae! Can you hear me?

697
00:51:42,335 --> 00:51:45,767
Room 310, she is awake.

698
00:51:45,767 --> 00:51:48,261
- Yi Jae!
- Yi Jae!

699
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:51,361
Are you awake?

700
00:51:51,361 --> 00:51:52,452
You okay?

701
00:51:52,452 --> 00:51:54,527
Do you recognize me?

702
00:51:55,597 --> 00:51:58,301
Why are you dressed like that?

703
00:51:58,301 --> 00:52:00,784
I'm not dead yet.

704
00:52:00,784 --> 00:52:05,817
Yi Jae...

705
00:52:05,817 --> 00:52:08,739
Yi Jae...

706
00:52:13,282 --> 00:52:14,621
Yi Jae.

707
00:52:15,372 --> 00:52:19,108
Your dad must've woken you before he left.

708
00:52:45,208 --> 00:52:48,173
<i>A life touched by regret</i>

709
00:52:48,173 --> 00:52:52,333
<i>can fall apart at any moment.</i>

710
00:53:04,136 --> 00:53:07,713
<i>You know The Fox and the Grapes?</i>

711
00:53:07,713 --> 00:53:11,530
<i>A fox wanted grapes hanging way up high.</i>

712
00:53:11,530 --> 00:53:14,547
<i>He tried everything, but couldn't reach them.</i>

713
00:53:14,547 --> 00:53:16,940
<i>Call me instead.</i>

714
00:53:16,940 --> 00:53:19,199
<i>Wherever you are, I'll come running.</i>

715
00:53:21,413 --> 00:53:24,169
<i>Stand on my shoulders.</i>

716
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:40,099
<i>My regret...</i>

717
00:53:42,709 --> 00:53:44,450
<i>was me all along.</i>

718
00:54:07,693 --> 00:54:09,682
<i>You bastard.</i>

719
00:54:14,206 --> 00:54:16,546
God, I'm an idiot.

720
00:54:22,114 --> 00:54:24,278
[Jaejae Noodles]
<i>I'm Ian Woo, a filmmaker.</i>

721
00:54:24,278 --> 00:54:26,291
<i>- It's an honor to be on this show.</i>
- Mom!

722
00:54:26,291 --> 00:54:27,348
Mom!

723
00:54:27,348 --> 00:54:28,975
Mom!

724
00:54:28,975 --> 00:54:30,846
- Look at this!
- What?

725
00:54:30,846 --> 00:54:31,905
Look at the TV!

726
00:54:31,905 --> 00:54:35,333
<i>You fell while digging clams on the mudflats.</i>

727
00:54:35,333 --> 00:54:39,619
Isn't that Soo Bin with Yi Jae?

728
00:54:42,066 --> 00:54:46,995
<i>That's what gets our viewers laughing.</i>

729
00:54:46,995 --> 00:54:48,891
What the heck?

730
00:54:48,891 --> 00:54:51,199
Why is he on that show?

731
00:55:06,943 --> 00:55:09,308
Why say no? That's what's weird.

732
00:55:09,308 --> 00:55:11,208
Why should I say yes?

733
00:55:11,208 --> 00:55:15,320
You said dreams aren't first-come,
first-served.

734
00:55:15,320 --> 00:55:16,786
Maybe yours just took longer.

735
00:55:16,786 --> 00:55:20,686
I'm not young anymore. I can't live on dreams.

736
00:55:20,686 --> 00:55:22,962
That's insane.

737
00:55:22,962 --> 00:55:24,373
What about me?

738
00:55:24,373 --> 00:55:26,840
Hey, you're different.

739
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:29,850
Your dream's still alive. Mine is over.

740
00:55:29,850 --> 00:55:33,420
And your dad might back you up.

741
00:55:33,420 --> 00:55:35,237
You have it easier.

742
00:55:35,237 --> 00:55:36,860
Excuses.

743
00:55:37,879 --> 00:55:42,237
So I'm only doing this
because I have a safety net?

744
00:55:42,237 --> 00:55:44,483
That's not what I meant.

745
00:55:47,296 --> 00:55:48,580
I'm sorry.

746
00:55:48,580 --> 00:55:51,482
I was out of line.

747
00:55:52,787 --> 00:55:56,531
Passing up a chance... that's what's insane.

748
00:55:56,531 --> 00:55:58,388
You've done it before.

749
00:55:58,388 --> 00:56:01,314
I guess Soo Bin is here to make it up to you.

750
00:56:01,314 --> 00:56:04,385
- Think of it that way.
- He didn't take it. I let it go.

751
00:56:04,385 --> 00:56:06,758
You gave up the exam and ran after him...

752
00:56:06,758 --> 00:56:08,545
Sim Yu Geon.

753
00:56:12,152 --> 00:56:14,575
And look how you lived after that.

754
00:56:14,575 --> 00:56:17,521
Don't those years feel wasted?

755
00:56:18,508 --> 00:56:21,852
Value yourself a little.

756
00:56:21,852 --> 00:56:24,353
Stop calling yourself pathetic.

757
00:56:28,422 --> 00:56:30,755
Where are you going?

758
00:56:30,755 --> 00:56:32,961
To make a living.

759
00:56:34,435 --> 00:56:37,006
- I'm here for my shift.
- Start with the dishes.

760
00:56:37,006 --> 00:56:38,515
Yes, sir.

761
00:56:47,613 --> 00:56:49,368
[Here Comes Yi Jae]
[Viewer Board]

762
00:56:49,368 --> 00:56:52,695
"Woo Fox picked my heart, not grapes."

763
00:56:52,695 --> 00:56:57,416
"Ian Woo, you're dangerously perfect."

764
00:56:57,416 --> 00:56:59,424
What is happening?

765
00:56:59,424 --> 00:57:01,223
Yes!

766
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:04,400
We got it! Hold on...

767
00:57:04,400 --> 00:57:05,430
Yeah, CP.

768
00:57:05,430 --> 00:57:07,596
Are you at your desk?

769
00:57:08,578 --> 00:57:11,149
Gosh. You washed up here again?

770
00:57:11,149 --> 00:57:13,063
Is this overtime or a sleepover?

771
00:57:13,063 --> 00:57:14,733
A sleepover.

772
00:57:14,733 --> 00:57:17,839
Hey, that's not important.

773
00:57:17,839 --> 00:57:20,857
When was the last time you blew up like this?

774
00:57:20,857 --> 00:57:23,050
Never.

775
00:57:23,050 --> 00:57:25,195
I've never seen high schoolers watch my show.

776
00:57:25,195 --> 00:57:30,334
I know.
His clips were all over our team chat today.

777
00:57:31,768 --> 00:57:33,235
What?

778
00:57:33,235 --> 00:57:36,985
But... Isn't Woo Soo Bin that guy?

779
00:57:36,985 --> 00:57:38,858
Your first love?

780
00:57:39,764 --> 00:57:41,295
What did he say?

781
00:57:41,295 --> 00:57:43,402
Did he miss you? Still love you?

782
00:57:43,402 --> 00:57:45,219
What are you talking about?

783
00:57:45,219 --> 00:57:47,879
A first-love reunion?

784
00:57:48,585 --> 00:57:50,609
You know I love those!

785
00:57:50,609 --> 00:57:52,640
Hey, I have to go.

786
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:54,266
Lay off the romance novels.

787
00:57:54,266 --> 00:57:56,681
Don't tell anyone.

788
00:57:56,681 --> 00:58:00,202
- Hello, sir?
- Now I'm hooked.

789
00:58:00,202 --> 00:58:02,592
Right. Work.

790
00:58:08,224 --> 00:58:10,556
Yeah, come in.

791
00:58:12,996 --> 00:58:15,021
- Hey.
- You're here.

792
00:58:15,021 --> 00:58:16,305
Sit.

793
00:58:16,305 --> 00:58:18,626
What's this?

794
00:58:18,626 --> 00:58:20,058
Beer in broad daylight?

795
00:58:20,058 --> 00:58:21,759
Trying to butter me up?

796
00:58:21,759 --> 00:58:23,597
A chicken bribe?

797
00:58:25,631 --> 00:58:27,255
It's crispy.

798
00:58:27,255 --> 00:58:29,019
Well...

799
00:58:29,019 --> 00:58:32,296
You know that director, don't you?

800
00:58:34,094 --> 00:58:35,105
What?

801
00:58:35,105 --> 00:58:38,110
- Yeah?
- No, I don't.

802
00:58:38,110 --> 00:58:41,200
- What director?
- You think I'm clueless, right?

803
00:58:41,200 --> 00:58:42,510
Hey.

804
00:58:42,510 --> 00:58:46,980
I watched you two for hours in the edit room.

805
00:58:49,037 --> 00:58:50,274
Yeah...

806
00:58:50,274 --> 00:58:53,120
We went to school together.
We're not exactly close.

807
00:58:53,951 --> 00:58:57,162
Perfect. Get him back on the show.

808
00:58:57,162 --> 00:58:58,956
What? No way.

809
00:58:58,956 --> 00:59:01,704
- Repeats aren't fun.
- Come on.

810
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,554
Don't be dense.

811
00:59:03,554 --> 00:59:05,294
Let's ride this.

812
00:59:05,294 --> 00:59:07,011
Before another show grabs him.

813
00:59:07,011 --> 00:59:09,883
- Don't hand him over.
- Let them have him.

814
00:59:09,883 --> 00:59:13,087
This season has fall leaves,
harvests, and plenty to cover.

815
00:59:13,087 --> 00:59:15,171
Are we just worshipping some director?

816
00:59:15,171 --> 00:59:17,548
Let's go plan the next item.

817
00:59:17,548 --> 00:59:20,354
If this works, we get our own slot.

818
00:59:20,354 --> 00:59:23,788
This is our big chance.

819
00:59:23,788 --> 00:59:24,926
<i>Ju Yi Jae.</i>

820
00:59:24,926 --> 00:59:27,266
<i>Bring him back, no matter what.</i>

821
00:59:27,266 --> 00:59:29,530
<i>Fail, and don't come back to Seoul.</i>

822
00:59:29,530 --> 00:59:32,463
<i>He's somewhere in Bunam right now.</i>

823
00:59:32,463 --> 00:59:34,785
<i>Book him. No excuses.</i>

824
00:59:49,878 --> 00:59:52,342
[Welcome to Bunam City]

825
01:00:50,555 --> 01:00:52,501
Excuse me.

826
01:01:55,983 --> 01:01:57,141
<i>Hit me.</i>

827
01:01:57,141 --> 01:01:58,254
<i>I had hope...</i>

828
01:01:58,254 --> 01:02:00,038
<i>How much will you tell me?</i>

829
01:02:00,038 --> 01:02:03,098
<i>I'll tell you everything I know.</i>

830
01:02:03,098 --> 01:02:04,275
<i>Who are you?</i>

831
01:02:04,275 --> 01:02:05,675
<i>I keep thinking about you.</i>

832
01:02:05,675 --> 01:02:08,188
<i>Want to be my friend?</i>

833
01:02:08,188 --> 01:02:11,598
<i>I'm not asking for understanding
or forgiveness now.</i>

834
01:02:11,598 --> 01:02:13,998
<i>You jerk. Why keep following me?</i>

835
01:02:13,998 --> 01:02:16,435
<i>I never forgot you.</i>

836
01:02:16,435 --> 01:02:19,119
<i>Why am I here?</i>

837
01:02:19,119 --> 01:02:22,439
<i>You drank with me.</i>
